         <div class="documentTop SubjectPage">            
                     
            <h1>International Collaboration<br /> on Education and Research</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/Upload/KD/Temabilder/Internasjonalt/Internasjonalt.jpg" alt="" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">Norway participates in a range of international collaborative efforts concerning education and research. International collaboration is critical for strengthening knowledge and competence development.



</p>
            <img src="/Upload/KD/Temabilder/Internasjonalt/Internasjonalt.jpg" alt="" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p>Through collaboration, we can contribute to better international practice, and also benefit from increased access to knowledge and technology. Such activity creates better cross-cultural understanding, improved contact between countries, the building of personal relationships and professional networks.&nbsp; Norway cooperate within the EU/EEA, the Council of Europe, the Nordic Council of Ministers, the OECD and UNESCO, and also with individual countries.&nbsp; </p></div>
	    <div style="clear:both"></div>
	      
         </div>
         
         
                                
        
        
        
                            
    <div id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_divPageContent" class="documentBody">  
                

<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/KD/Ingressbilder/Internasjonalt/norden_flagg-jpg.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/kd/Selected-topics/International-Collaboration-on-Education/nordic-cooperation.html?id=535151">Nordic cooperation</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               One of the goals of the Nordic Council of Ministers is to create a sound education and research community in the Nordic region. A central role in this is played by the strategy of the ministers of education and research for the period 2008-2010, “The Nordic region – a leading dynamic region of knowledge and competence”.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/Upload/KD/Ingressbilder/Internasjonalt/EU_flagg1.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/kd/Selected-topics/International-Collaboration-on-Education/Europe.html?id=279694">Europe</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               After the EEA Agreement entered into force in 1994, extending the single European market to include the EFTA states, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein, Norway’s cooperation with the EU has been considerably reinforced and extended in several areas. 
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/Upload/KD/Ingressbilder/Internasjonalt/oecd.100_jpg.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/kd/Selected-topics/International-Collaboration-on-Education/oecd.html?id=86728">OECD</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               Collaboration between the OECD and the Ministry of Education and Research is based on the knowledge that both individuals and nations draw social and economic benefit from education. 

            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/Upload/KD/Ingressbilder/Internasjonalt/Fn_foto_karachi.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/kd/Selected-topics/International-Collaboration-on-Education/unesco.html?id=279650">UNESCO</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               UNESCO regards education as one of the most effective instruments to combat poverty. Norway is considerably involved in the programme Education for All (EFA)  – both through cooperation with individual countries and in playing a proactive role in UNESCO.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    

